     Technical Implementation Strategy

     Architecture Alignment with Existing Demo

     Following your Formula Manager pattern, the Delivery system will use:

     Three-Column Layout Structure

     - Left (20%): Driver/Vehicle directory with status filtering
     - Middle (60%): Route planning workspace with drag-drop optimization
     - Right (20%): Order queue with smart batching suggestions

     Context-Based State Management

     - DeliveryManagementContext: Central state for orders, routes, drivers, and real-time tracking
     - Real-time updates using WebSocket connections for live tracking
     - Integration with existing ProductFormulaContext for order data

     Component Architecture Using Excalibrr

     - GraviGrid for order lists, driver schedules, and performance tables
     - Horizontal/Vertical for complex layouts and responsive design  
     - GraviButton for route actions and driver assignments
     - Custom drag-drop components for route optimization
     - Integration with mapping libraries (Mapbox/Google Maps) via iframes

     Data Models & Relationships

     Core Entities

     interface DeliveryOrder {
       id: string;
       customerId: string;
       products: OrderItem[];
       deliveryAddress: Address;
       timeWindow: TimeWindow;
       priority: 'LOW' | 'MEDIUM' | 'HIGH' | 'URGENT';
       specialInstructions: string;
       weight: number;
       status: OrderStatus;
     }

     interface Driver {
       id: string;
       name: string;
       phoneNumber: string;
       vehicleId: string;
       status: 'AVAILABLE' | 'ON_ROUTE' | 'BREAK' | 'OFFLINE';
       currentLocation: GeoLocation;
       performanceMetrics: DriverMetrics;
     }

     interface DeliveryRoute {
       id: string;
       driverId: string;
       orders: DeliveryOrder[];
       optimizedStops: RouteStop[];
       estimatedDuration: number;
       status: 'DRAFT' | 'ASSIGNED' | 'IN_PROGRESS' | 'COMPLETED';
       realTimeUpdates: RouteProgress;
     }

